reviewText: You do not received honor recognition badge on your certificate after completion. Many students posted on the discussion forum and reported it to the instructor. No response is given if they even aware of the issue. Please look into this and fix.

T​his is probably the worst course I have taken on Coursera. I wouldn't recommend it to anyone. It was exceptionally boring and tedious. Too much of the content was geared toward knowing the name of a tab in the Ribbon even though Powerpoint only shows you the correct tabs for your context anyway. Too much emphasis was on how to add every effect to your presentation with no guidance for when you would want to use them or avoid them. This course wanted me to download a new file every few minutes even though I barely manipulated each one.
Sure it would be best to use the paid version of the app. Unable to complete most of the exercises in the week 4 portion.
Very informative however the videos are too wordy, making it difficult to digest. Sometimes it's too hard to get through a video
Good course and Good info just need to be an Arabic subtitle
First and 4th week were not soo much understandable then 2nd and 3rd one.
This course does not offer Microsoft's logo in its certificates.

I really enjoyed this course although there was a lot of material in one video at a time and some of the test questions were not right and some a little confusing. The instructor was fantastic. Overall I give the course a four stars out of five. Thank you for the great study.
C​omplete and accurate . It should be considered to offer honors for assignements

Great course for brushing up MS Office skill and learning some neat tricks. The course is broken down into small bits so it is easy to work on it on your own pace. However, it is broken down into VERY small sections so it felt a little tedious.Also, some of the quizes require to read the very fine detail without much visual instructions.It will be nice if there was more visual downloadable contents to review later without going through the videos each time you want to revisit some subjects.
I would love to recommend this course for newbie and if you want to remaster Power Point skills. Week 3 and 4 syllabus is really beneficial for Power Point understanding.

I learned a lot in this course to make a presentation in a professional way. This is a summary of what I learned, and it means a lot.I recommend this disc to anyone who is trying to learn to do a presentation, and to anyone who likes to make a PPT in a professional way.
And this training course is completely free, and I think it is worth a lot to learn in any educational centre or otherwise. Thank you, Microsoft, and thank you for this wonderful and more than a wonderful training course.

Honestly, Coursera is the best platform for learning new skills. However, I gained confidence after taking some specialization courses. In addition, I truly appreciate all the great instructors for amazing skill sharing. Hence, I am applying all the skills and knowledge in my practical day-to-day life which I have learned in Coursera.
